parameters: Ah, Faris! I came because I was a little curious.

Oh, Konoha. I confirmed it, but as expected,
something terrible happened. The Treasure Sword
has been stolen.

Eh?! So it was really stolen after all! That
person, lied to me...!

I told you so, didn't I? Well, never mind. Just
find the person who stole it. It would be good if
you could at least identify their appearance.

He was still a young boy. I think he was human,
but he had a pretty strong name, Meeguru.

What's this? Could it be that we know each other?
To think you even revealed your name.

No, that's not it. I didn't mention it earlier,
but the other day, I was surrounded by monsters
during a subjugation and had no choice but to
cooperate.

I see, so that's how it is. Well, never mind.
Let's make urgent arrangements for that Meeguru.

I don't think he understands the importance of
that treasure sword, so I don't think he will use
it for anything bad. But we need to find him
quickly so that it doesn't end up in the wrong
hands.

That's right. If it falls into the hands of
bandits, it will inevitably end up in the
possession of demons. We must avoid that at all
costs.

I also have responsibility. I'll help search for
Meeguru.
Yes, Konoha, I'm counting on you!

That Meeguru guy! He's such an idiot...! We have
to find him... but I wonder where he is...

Maybe it would be a good idea to gather
information at the tavern in the Golden City for
now. Let's ask around for places where those thief
wannabes might hang out.

Well, I wonder if the final monster is around
here...?

There's something... Is that... rummaging through
graves? For a monster...
Are you... by any chance, a grave robber...?
Hehe... No way... Tha... Ah, hey! Behind!! Behind!

Hmph, I won't fall for that. This is a prestigious
graveyard, and yet you're a grave robber.
Idiot! That's not it! There's a monster behind us!

So this really is an enemy. This creature is a
target for extermination, but we're surrounded
now.

Geez, don't bring monsters along. I'll take care
of this one, so I'll leave that one to you,
Magical Girl.

I am Meeguru! The future Bandit aspirant, Meeguru-
sama!

Phew, we managed to defeat it. Are you okay,
Meeguru?
Of course, this kind of monster is no big deal.

Before we talk about the grave robbing incident...
I can't just let this slide, but didn't you
mention earlier that you aspire to be a bandit?
Are you serious?

Ah, I'm serious. That's why I'm here, to find
treasure and earn recognition as a bandit from
Dartle!

Sigh... Being a bandit isn't the same as being a
regular thief, you know? It's like selling your
soul to demons! Absolutely not!

What's the big deal about that! Being human is too
weak. It's fine for you since you're a magical
girl, though.
I need more and more power!

Anyway, leave the things you stole from the graves
here. These belong to the territory of Faris.

Hey hey, I haven't stolen anything yet! We were
just interrupted, you know.

...I understand. Well, I'll believe you for now.
Let's forget about being a bandit for the time
being and reconsider. After all, we only live
once...

Hehe, you're a good person, but I think being too
kind might not be a good thing, Konoha-san. Well
then,

Now that we're done with subjugating the magical
beasts, we should report to Faris. Oh, and we
should also mention the grave robbing incident,
just in case.

It didn't seem like there was anything, but... I
found something good. Hehe.

Don't let your guard down. It's a good thing we
managed to defeat the enemy and escape.
I can't just leave you alone, so I'm going now.

Wait... I can't just let it slide. Didn't you say
you wanted to become a bandit earlier? Are you
serious?

Ah, I'm serious. That's why I found this treasure
here, so that I can be recognized by the Bandits
of Dartle!

Haa... Bandits aren't just ordinary thieves, you
know? It's like selling your soul to demons!
Absolutely not!

What's the big deal about that! You're too weak as
a human. It's fine for you since you're a magical
girl, though.
I need more and more power!

By the way, leave the things you stole from the
graves here. These belong to the territory of
Faris.

Hey hey, I haven't stolen anything yet! You got in
the way, you know.

...I understand. I owe you for helping me, so for
now, let's put aside the bandit thing and
reconsider. After all, we only live once...

Hehe, you're a good person, but I think you're too
kind, Konoha-san. Well then,

We'll have to start over with subjugating the
magical beasts. After we're done, we should just
report about the grave robbing, right?

It didn't seem like there was anything, but... I
found something good. Hehe.
